<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-2745] the gsp template can not support unicode(utf-8)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-2745</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;a test gsp file is (chinese encoding):&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;html&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;head&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;meta http-equiv=&quot;Content-Type&quot; content=&quot;text/html; charset=utf-8&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;title&amp;gt;&amp;#27979;&amp;#35797;&amp;#39029;&amp;lt;/title&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/head&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;body&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;%&lt;br/&gt;
    print &quot;groopvy &amp;#27979;&amp;#35797;&amp;#39029;&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
%&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/body&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/html&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After browser the groovy.servlet.TemplateServlet source code,I find that the service method only set the ContentType to &quot;text/html&quot; .There no information about encoding.&lt;br/&gt;
So I add the encoding support for it,you can see the attachment(diff format),and you can configure it throgh the web.xml&lt;/p&gt;</description>
